get weights

## calculate monthly sd for each stock
rw.ret = rw.ret %>% group_by(permno,yymm) %>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(sd=sd(ret))%>% ungroup()
rw.ret = rw.ret %>% group_by(permno) %>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(lag.sd=lag(sd,1))%>% ungroup()
rw.ret = rw.ret %>% group_by(permno,yymm)%>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(lag.sd=first(lag.sd))%>% ungroup()
## get weights
rw.ret = rw.ret %>% filter(!is.na(lag.sd)) %>%group_by(date)%>% 
  mutate(wgt= (1/lag.sd)/sum(1/lag.sd))%>% ungroup()
# calculate the cumulative returns of each individual stock over each month
rw.ret = rw.ret %>% 
  group_by(yymm,permno) %>% 
  arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(cumret=cumprod(ret+1)) %>% ungroup()
rw.ret = rw.ret %>% arrange(date,permno)
head(rw.ret)

# handling missing data

mutate(ipo=date[which(!is.na(ret))[1]]) %>% ungroup()

vw index in 2013

vw = mystock %>% mutate(me=prc*shrout) %>% select(permno, date, ret, me) 
# handling missing returns 
vw.ret = spread(vw[,c("permno","date","ret")],permno,ret)
vw.ret = gather(vw.ret,key=permno,value=ret,-date)
vw.ret = vw.ret %>% group_by(permno) %>% arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(ipo=date[which(!is.na(ret))[1]]) %>% ungroup()
vw.ret = vw.ret %>% filter(date>=ipo) %>% arrange(permno,date)
vw.ret = vw.ret %>% 
  mutate(ret=ifelse(is.na(ret),0,ret))

# seperate market cap into another dataframe and merge back onto returns
vw.me = vw %>% select(permno,date,me)
vw = vw.ret %>% left_join(vw.me,by=c("permno","date"))

  group_by(permno) %>%
  arrange(date) %>%

  filter(date>='2013-01-01'&date<='2013-12-31')

crsp.vw = crsp.vw %>% 
  mutate(yymm=substr(date,1,7)) %>%
  group_by(permno,yymm) %>%
  arrange(date) %>% 
  mutate(lag.me=first(lag.me)) %>% ungroup()
# fill lag.me with 0 if NA
crsp.vw = crsp.vw %>% mutate(lag.me=ifelse(is.na(lag.me),0,lag.me))
# calculate weight
crsp.vw = crsp.vw %>% 
  group_by(date) %>%
  mutate(wgt=lag.me/sum(lag.me,na.rm=T)) %>%
  ungroup()
crsp.vw = crsp.vw %>% group_by(permno) %>% ungroup()
# calculate cumulative rets for each stock in each month
crsp.vw = crsp.vw %>% 
  group_by(yymm,permno) %>% 
  arrange(date) %>%
  mutate(cumret=cumprod(ret+1)) %>% ungroup()
# construct vw index
crsp.vw = crsp.vw %>% arrange(date,permno) %>%
  mutate(vw=wgt*cumret)

crsp.vw = crsp.vw %>%

  1. with function in part a.
# calculate var of each stock and cov between each two stocks
var1=var(mystock.var$AAPL)*252
var2=var(mystock.var$BABA)*252
var3=var(mystock.var$GE)*252
var4=var(mystock.var$IBM)*252
var5=var(mystock.var$KO)*252
var6=var(mystock.var$MSFT)*252
cov12=cov(mystock.var$AAPL,mystock.var$BABA)*252
cov13=cov(mystock.var$AAPL,mystock.var$GE)*252
cov14=cov(mystock.var$AAPL,mystock.var$IBM)*252
cov15=cov(mystock.var$AAPL,mystock.var$KO)*252
cov16=cov(mystock.var$AAPL,mystock.var$MSFT)*252
cov23=cov(mystock.var$BABA,mystock.var$GE)*252
cov24=cov(mystock.var$BABA,mystock.var$IBM)*252
cov25=cov(mystock.var$BABA,mystock.var$KO)*252
cov26=cov(mystock.var$BABA,mystock.var$MSFT)*252
cov34=cov(mystock.var$GE,mystock.var$IBM)*252
cov35=cov(mystock.var$GE,mystock.var$KO)*252
cov36=cov(mystock.var$GE,mystock.var$MSFT)*252
cov45=cov(mystock.var$IBM,mystock.var$KO)*252
cov46=cov(mystock.var$IBM,mystock.var$MSFT)*252
cov56=cov(mystock.var$KO,mystock.var$MSFT)*252

# assign weight to each stock
w1=0.1
w2=0.25
w3=0.1
w4=0.15
w5=0.2
w6=0.2

# do the calculation
var_port=w1^2*var1+w2^2*var2+w3^2*var3+w4^2*var4+w5^2*var5+w6^2*var6+
  2*w1*w2*cov12+2*w1*w3*cov13+2*w1*w4*cov14+2*w1*w5*cov15+2*w1*w6*cov16+
  2*w2*w3*cov23+2*w2*w4*cov24+2*w2*w5*cov25+2*w2*w6*cov26+
  2*w3*w4*cov34+2*w3*w5*cov35+2*w3*w6*cov36+
  2*w4*w5*cov45+2*w4*w6*cov46+
  2*w5*w6*cov56

  select(permno,date,ret) %>%
  mutate(permno=as.character(permno))

# filter data
crsp.sample = filter(crsp.sample, crsp.sample$permno==39731|permno==79089|permno==83148, crsp.sample$date>="2017-01-01"&
crsp.sample$date<="2018-12-31")

# check missing data
crsp.ret = spread(crsp.sample[,c("permno","date","ret")], permno, ret)
crsp.ret = gather(crsp.ret,key=permno,value=ret,-date)
crsp.ret = crsp.ret %>% 
  mutate(ret=ifelse(is.na(ret),0,ret))

# calculate return, sd
df1 = crsp.ret %>% group_by(permno) %>%
  summarise(ret.daily=mean(ret), sd.daily=sd(ret))
# calculate cov, cor
crsp.ret = spread(crsp.sample[,c("permno","date","ret")], permno, ret)
cov.daily= cov(crsp.ret[,2:ncol(crsp.ret)])

  1. get portfolio return and risk with different weights
tmp = crsp.sample %>% select(permno,date,ret)
ret.sd = tmp %>% group_by(permno) %>% 
  summarise(sd=sqrt(252)*sd(ret),
            ret=252*mean(ret))
tmp = tmp %>% spread(permno,ret)
cov = cov(tmp[,c(2,3,4)])*252
cor = cor(tmp[,c(2,3,4)])
dd = NULL
for (i in seq(0,1,0.01)){
  for (j in seq(0,1-i,0.01)){
    k = 1-i-j
      w = c(i,j,k)
      wm = matrix(w,1)
      tmpsd = sqrt(wm %*% cov %*% t(wm))
      tmpret = sum(w * ret.sd$ret)
      rst = c(w,tmpsd,tmpret)
      dd = rbind(dd,rst)
  }
}
colnames(dd)=c("w1","w2","w3","sd","ret")
dd=as.data.frame(dd)
dd= dd[order(dd$sd),]
plot(dd$ret~dd$sd,type='p')

show the results with weights (39731,79089,83148)=(0.4,0.2,0.4) and weights(39731,79089,83148)=c(0.8,0.1,0.1)

  1. efficient frontier
dd.r = round(dd,3)

ef = dd.r %>% group_by(ret) %>% summarise(sd = min(sd))
plot(ef$ret~ef$sd,type='l', main='Efficient Frontior')

  1. get the portfolio allocation that has the highest sharpe ratio
dd = dd %>% mutate(rf = 0,
                   sr = (ret-rf)/sd)
cml = dd[which(dd$sr==max(dd$sr)),]
